I"³<p>If a git repo has submodules in it there are two options I use for cloning the repo and cloning the submodules in it. The first method is cloning the submodules during the original clone.</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git clone <span class="nt">--recursive</span> &lt;url&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>The second method is to clone the repo and then clone the submodules.</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git clone &lt;url&gt;
<span class="nb">cd</span> &lt;repo&gt;
git submodule update <span class="nt">--init</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
:ET